reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Value for the Price
reviews.reviewText: These cables worked great for this new Surface Go3 stands we purchased that allows you to connect a Brother label printer to the stand. We needed to connect the Brother printer via USB-C to USB-B and these cables worked perfectly for our use case.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 27, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I couldn't believe I'd find a vintage-adaptable cable, but here it is!
reviews.reviewText: I needed a cable to connect my AlphaSmart 3000 keyboard (remember those? They date from the last century) to my new Mac. I use the AlphaSmart to write brief notes when I don't want a light-up keyboard to disrupt my diurnal rhythms, such as keying in notes from a fencing lesson late at night. It's also very light, so good to take on long trips or hikes. Anyway, the cable that the now-defunct company furnished to allow me to download text to my computer ends in a USB-B connector, and my new Mac has a USB-C socket. I figured I'd never find a cable that would directly connect my dear old AlphaSmart to my Mac. I thought I'd need one of those awkward USB-C to USB-C cables. But I found it! I had to look carefully at the pictures to make sure the plus was exactly right, but i ordered it, it was inexpensive, it arrived the next day, and when I went to connect the two devices, it worked perfectly. Cool!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 23, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Super service from Cable Matters
reviews.reviewText: I ordered a USB-C to -A cable from Cable Matters with fulfillment (packing and shipping) by Amazon from one of their warehouses. A couple of days later I received an empty envelope--no cable or packing slip or anything. I contacted Cable Matters via email and explained the situation. I received a very nice reply from Chelsea saying that since fulfillment was by Amazon I should contact them at the phone number she supplied or via their contact page.I tried the number and got a message that, due to COVID-19, they weren't answering phone calls. I tried to do a "return for replacement" but no matter what option I selected the Amazon web page insisted that I return the missing product. Duh! I then tried their automated "chatbot" but twice ended up waiting endlessly for it to return from a "Give me a minute to check on that" reply.I gave up and contacted Cable Matters and explained the "Catch 22" I had encountered. Chelsea immediately replied, asking for my shipping address, saying that they would ship a cable directly to me from their stock. I complied and a short time later the cable was on its way to me.Thanks, Cable Matters and Chelsea. It's refreshing to find an Amazon partner merchant that truly accepts their customer's problem as their own.As for the cable, it's excellent quality and it works. What else can I say?

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Connecting smart phone to USB switch. No problems so far.
reviews.reviewText: I picked up one of these because I needed to connect a smart phone to a USB switch that uses type B jacks for the inputs. I have had no issues with Cable Matters products in the past, so I thought I'd start with their cable and see if it'll do the job. Not much to say - it's a USB cable, so it's either going to work or not work. So far mine has worked as expected.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cable Matters is a Reliable Brand
reviews.reviewText: I've use a number of USB cables from Cable Matters in an observatory for astronomy cameras. Condensation is a persistent problem and CM cables are far less problematic than some other brands we've tried. In the rare event of an early failure CM customer service quickly replaced the defective cable.
I was not able to find this cable at Staples or Best Buy.Happy that Amazon was able to fill the bill
Glad I bought this, it is now an extra as someone gave me one.
